n dust temperature at a constant far-infrared luminosity across z{\textasciitilde}1.5-4. We show that {SMGs} appear to behave as simple homologous systems in the far-infrared, having properties consistent with a centrally illuminated starburst. Our study provides strong support for an evolutionary link between the active, gas-rich {SMG} population at z{\textgreater}1 and the formation of massive, bulge-dominated galaxies across the history of the Universe.},
